Reasoning: The paper discusses proof techniques for bisimilarity and unique solution of equations in the context of process calculi such as CSP and CCS. This falls under the area of formal methods and theoretical computer science. The paper also discusses the application of these techniques to name-passing calculi such as the asynchronous pi-calculus, which suggests a focus on process calculi with communication. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), followed by cs.PL (Programming Languages), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory), and cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science).
